title: Formation of Activation Products in Interactions of Medium Energy Protons with Na, Si, P, Cl, Ca and Fe.

x4freetext: Formation of Activation Products in Interactions of
Medium Energy Protons with Na, Si, P, Cl, Ca and Fe.
The Proton fluxes for E<200 MeV the Cross Section were
taken from a Cube Spline Fit.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.441, p.617 (1985)
Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.41, p.315 (1990)
Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.43, p.1019 (1992)
Rept: Centre d`Etudes Nucleaires, note, No.1466 (1971)

x4freetext: For E>200 MeV.
- By Authors - The Flux Values Obtained Via the
Formation of Na-24 were Compared with Those Via the
Na-22 and Zn-62 Monitor Reaction Products, and were
Found to be Consistent Within an Uncertainty of 3-6%.
The Svedberg Laboratory, Uppsala
Beam Energy 180 and 130 MeV. Seven Stacks, Each
Containing Up to 40 Foils were Irradiated.
Saturne National Laboratory.
Beam Energy 250 and 300 MeV.  Six Thin Stacks were
Irradiated.
Each Target (0.1 - 0.3 GRAMM/CM-SQ) Was
Sandwiched Between Thin, 50-100 Mumeters, Catcher Foils
To Avoid Cross Contamination.  The Target Foils
Or Pellet Thickness was Adopted Such That the Energy
Absorption did not Exceed 2 MeV.  1000 Mumeters
Aluminum and 100 Mumeters Copper Foils were Also Placed
In the Stack, Serving As Flux and Energy Monitors.
Last checking has been done.
DATE is corrected
The Total Uncertainty in the Proton Beam
Current was Estimated to be 10-15%. The Uncertainty in
The Peak Area Analysis was Generally 5-10%, in Weaker
Samples, However, Up to 54%.  Detector Efficiency
Uncertainty was Estimated to be 3-5%.  All the
Uncertainties were Combined in Quadrature.
The Uncertainty is Given in Authors` Tables.
Model Calculation with Alice-Ippe Code.
Experimental Data were Compared with Another
Investigations.
